ades. Yet Yamin challenges us to consider why these advances have failed to produce greater equality within and between nations, and how the human rights praxis must now urgently address threats to social and gender justice, in health and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHealth services accessibilityxLaw and legislationxHistory. 0aHuman rightsxHealth aspectsxHistory. 0aMedical policyxHistory. 0aRight to healthxHistory. 0aWomen's health servicesxLaw and legislationxHistory. 7aLAW / Health.2bisacsh  aand cultural rights.  aconstitutional law.  adevelopment.  aeconomic.  aglobal health.  aglobalization.  ahuman rights.  ainternational law.  amultilateralism.  aright to health.  asexual and reproductive health and rights.  asocial.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishz97831107048600 cprintz978150360541140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361131340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503611313423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503611313/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070486-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020